         <abstract>
            <p>The numbers $2N = 2(2)1000000$ are checked to determine if they can be written as the sum of two twin primes. Thirty-three numbers are found that cannot be so represented; they are all less than 5000. The largest number in the range $2N = 2(2)500000$ that can be written as the sum of two twin primes in only one way is $2N = 24098$.</p>
